sdp/verification/t-001@20260425t183959zc-verify.md:13:Implementation is correct. `BufferLoader` uses `OrderedDict[int, BufferRecord]` keyed by `id(record)` for O(1) LRU promotion. Load calls `_evict_lru()` before allocating when `len(self._lru) >= self.capacity`, ensuring the live set never exceeds capacity. `touch()` calls `move_to_end(key)`, correctly promoting to MRU. `on_sampler_free` removes the record from `_lru` so freed records don't count against capacity. `_evict_lru` pops the front (`last=False`) entry, sends `/b_free`, and clears `buffer_id` on the evicted record. Ordering is preserved correctly in all paths.
sdp/verification/t-001@20260425t183959zc-verify.md:20:- **Double-load edge case**: Calling `on_sampler_load` on a record already live in `_lru` silently overwrites the `_lru` entry with a new bufnum, leaking the old bufnum (never freed, no OSC `/b_free` sent). No test covers this.
sdp/verification/t-001@20260425t183959zc-verify.md:25:Follows established patterns in the file: `id(record)` as dict key matches how `on_sampler_free` de-registers. Default `capacity=64` matches the existing `start_bufnum=100` convention of sensible defaults. `_evict_lru` is a private helper following the `_` prefix convention used elsewhere. Module docstring updated to describe LRU semantics. Consistent with prior subtask deliverables (Za, Zb).
sdp/verification/t-001@20260425t183959zc-verify.md:39:- [ ] Double-load leaks old bufnum: calling `on_sampler_load` on an already-live record allocates a new bufnum and orphans the old one without `/b_free` — severity: minor
sdp/verification/t-001@20260425t183959zc-verify.md:46:1. **Double-load guard (minor)**: Consider checking `if id(record) in self._lru` at the top of `on_sampler_load` and either calling `on_sampler_free(record)` first or just re-touching and returning the existing bufnum. A test for this behavior would pin the contract.
sdp/verification/t-030@20260425t183959za-verify.md:13:Field `sampler_density: float = 0.0` is correctly added to `ArtistMode` at line 165 with a docstring that accurately describes the 0.0–1.0 semantics. `__post_init__` raises `ValueError` for any value outside the closed interval. `EVENING_REFLECTION` is the only mode that receives a non-zero value (`0.45`), which is semantically correct — it is the only mode that explicitly rotates the full quintet (`preferred_voices=SIGNATURE_VOICES`). All other modes default to 0.0 and do not list `sw_sampler` in their preferred voices. `apply_mode_to_commission` propagates the field as `mode_sampler_density` in the output dict.
sdp/verification/t-030@20260425t183959za-verify.md:24:- `apply_mode_to_commission` key name `mode_sampler_density` is consistent with the `mode_` prefix used for all other serialized mode fields.
sdp/verification/t-030@20260425t183959za-verify.md:34:- Default of 0.0 ensures full backward compatibility — existing `ArtistMode` instantiations without `sampler_density` are unaffected.
sdp/verification/t-030@20260425t183959za-verify.md:54:No issues to address. The implementation is clean and complete. If future modes are added that use `sw_sampler` in `preferred_voices`, remember to set `sampler_density > 0.0` for those modes — the current docstring makes this expectation explicit.
