sdp/verification/t-017@20260425t183959z-verify.md:12:The implementation accurately follows the requested formula: `floor(sampler_density * total_phrases) + Bernoulli(sampler_density)`. The `count_sampler_events` function in `sampler_scheduler.py` correctly applies this math and clamps the result to `[0, total_phrases]`. `duet_composer.py` correctly integrates this logic, reading the density from mode-based defaults or score metadata, and recording the resulting plan (count and phrase indices) back into the score metadata.
sdp/verification/t-017@20260425t183959z-verify.md:18:The new module `sampler_scheduler.py` follows project conventions for deterministic RNG seeding and metadata storage. The integration in `duet_composer.py` is surgical and fits within the existing `tracker_solo_song` flow.
sdp/verification/t-017@20260425t183959z-verify.md:24:The test suite `tests/test_sampler_scheduler.py` is comprehensive, covering edge cases (empty pieces, out-of-range densities) and providing a statistical verification of per-mode separation over 100-piece runs.
