sdp/verification/t-007@20260416t181925z-verify.md:13:Formula is exactly `v₀ · √(1 - α · (x - x_start) / (x_end - x_start))` as specified, applied via `event.tempo_mult *= math.sqrt(max(0.0, 1.0 - self.alpha * progress))`. Guard against negative under the radical via `max(0.0, ...)`. At onset (x = x_start), progress = 0 so tempo is unaffected; at end (x = 1.0), progress = 1.0 so attenuation is `√(1 - α) = √0.65 ≈ 0.806`. Both match the Friberg–Sundberg spec.
sdp/verification/t-007@20260416t181925z-verify.md:20:- Tests cover: curve shape at midpoint and endpoint, onset boundary (no change at x=0.75 since progress=0), and non-application on non-cadential phrase.
sdp/verification/t-007@20260416t181925z-verify.md:36:- `min(1.0, max(0.0, ...))` clamp on progress prevents extrapolation if `normalized_phrase_position > 1.0`.
