my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:5:CypherClaw's signature palette is a quartet: `sw_bell_warm`, `sw_bowed`, `sw_breath`, `sw_pad`. These are synthesis voices — every sound they make is generated from oscillators, filters, and envelopes. They have no memory of the room, no memory of yesterday, no memory of what just happened. Every piece is born from silence.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:7:This PRD adds a fifth signature voice — **`sw_sampler`** — that elevates the room itself, the artist's recorded history, and a curated found-sound library into a primary instrument. The sampler is **how CypherClaw metabolizes the room**: it listens continuously to the contact mic and room mic, captures fragments worth remembering, and replays those fragments granularly — stretched, transposed, scrubbed, with a dedicated effects bus — back into the live performance.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:19:1. **Granular by default, never one-shot.** The sampler is a granular voice with grain size 20–200 ms, density, position scrub, and pitch transpose. "Press button hear sample" is not a use case. Every play is a re-rendering through grains.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:21:3. **Effects-bus parity with the rest of the orchestra.** Sampler output routes through a dedicated effects bus (long delay, convolution reverb, spectral freeze, comb resonance to B fundamental). The effects shape the *character of the voice*, not just gloss on top.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:29:**In scope:** a granular SuperCollider voice (`sw_sampler`) with a dedicated effects bus; a sample library on disk with tag-based selection; a continuous live-capture daemon for contact/room mics; a self-quotation loop; integration with the existing artist-mode selector and cast planner so the sampler joins the signature quintet; metrics and anti-pattern detection for sampler over- or under-use.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:44:**Phase 2 — SuperCollider granular voice (CCS-009..CCS-014).** `sw_sampler.scd` SynthDef with grain-controlled buffer playback; buffer-management protocol for loading samples on demand; dedicated effects bus (delay + reverb + spectral freeze + comb-to-B); mix-engine integration so the sampler routes through the master bus. End of phase: sending OSC `/s_new sw_sampler bufnum=N grain_size=80ms density=12 pitch=0` plays a granular cloud audible through the speakers.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:48:**Phase 4 — Composer integration (CCS-022..CCS-028).** Mode-driven sampler density (solitary heavy, working light, etc.); `select_sample()` wired into cast/instrument-patch path so the composer treats the sampler as a first-class voice; self-quotation loop captures composer output when arc-payoff is high; keyboard/Theramini capture during human play; per-mode effects-bus presets; operator diagnostics surface currently-active samples. End of phase: pieces start to noticeably *cite themselves* across sessions, and the room's acoustic history becomes audible material.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:50:**Phase 5 — Verification + observability (CCS-029..CCS-033).** Per-piece sampler-event metrics; anti-pattern detection for sampler dominating (over-quote) or never appearing (silent quintet member); a sample-usage journal that records which samples played in which pieces with what transformations; end-to-end smoke test on cypherclaw confirming the daemon is capturing, the selector is choosing, the synth is playing, and the self-listener is observing the right output peaks. End of phase: composer can demonstrate a piece that uses 1 self-quotation + 1 room-capture + 1 library sample, all selector-chosen, all routed through the effects bus, all surfaced in the diagnostics dashboard.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:54:- `my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md` — the rendering layer; sampler events flow through the same RenderPass (R-rules respect `role="sampler"` with grid_locked=False so phrasing applies, but R8 microtiming is dampened on grain-time-scale events).
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:57:- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/master_bus.py` and `mix_engine.py` — the sampler effects bus routes its summed output through the master, respecting amp/compression caps.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:65:- **New** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/sampler_effects.scd` — dedicated effects bus SynthDef chain
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:68:- **New** `my-claw/tests/test_sample_library.py` — selector, tag parsing, mode-aware filtering
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:73:- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/instrument_patches.py` — patches reference sampler effects-bus presets
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:91:| CCS-003 | Implement `SampleLibrary` on-disk store backed by `index.sqlite` with tag/source/pitch/mood-range queries. | MUST | T1 | - `SampleLibrary(root: Path)` opens / creates `index.sqlite` with table `samples` carrying every `SampleRecord` field plus full-text-search index on `character_tags`<br/>- `library.add(record)` persists row + verifies file presence<br/>- `library.find(source=, character_any=, character_all=, pitch_band=, arc_phase=, mood_range=, limit=)` returns ordered list (most recent first within match set)<br/>- tests cover insert, query by each filter, empty-result path, and corrupted-DB rebuild |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:96:| CCS-008 | Register `voice_sampler` character in `character_registry.py` with `voice.synth = "sw_sampler"`, `voice.role = "sampler"`, default register, and per-mode gain overrides. | MUST | T1 | - `character_registry.py` gains `voice_sampler` entry with synth=`sw_sampler`, role=`sampler`, register=`[36, 84]`, params containing default grain_size_ms, density, pitch_transpose<br/>- character is selectable by `select_cast_ids` when `preferred_synths` includes `sw_sampler`<br/>- tests verify registration and selection through cast planner |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:97:| CCS-009 | Implement `sw_sampler.scd` granular SynthDef with bufnum, grain-size, density, position-scrub, pitch-transpose, attack/release envelope, and effects-bus send. | MUST | T1 | - SynthDef args: `bufnum`, `amp` (default 0.5), `grain_size_ms` (default 80, range 20–200), `density` (default 12 grains/sec), `position` (0..1 normalized), `position_rate` (scrub speed), `pitch_transpose_semitones` (default 0), `pitch_jitter_semitones` (default 0.1), `attack_sec` (default 0.05), `release_sec` (default 0.2), `gate` (default 1, sustained), `out_bus` (default 0), `fx_send` (default 0.4)<br/>- `doneAction:2` self-frees on envelope end<br/>- compiled `sw_sampler.scsyndef` lives in `synthesis/synthdefs/`<br/>- SC-side test (`my-claw/supercollider/test_sw_sampler.scd`) renders 2-second clip from a known buffer and verifies non-silence + spectral characteristics<br/>- gate=0 triggers release tail correctly |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:99:| CCS-011 | Implement `sampler_effects.scd` dedicated effects-bus SynthDef chain: long delay (1/4 to 1/2 measure), convolution reverb (FreeVerb fallback if no IR loaded), spectral freeze (PV_Freeze), comb-resonance tuned to B fundamental (61.74 Hz). | MUST | T1 | - SynthDef `sw_sampler_fx` reads from a stereo bus and writes to master bus<br/>- args: `delay_time` (sec, default 0.5), `delay_feedback` (0..0.85, default 0.55), `verb_mix` (default 0.35), `room_size` (default 0.7), `freeze_amount` (0..1, default 0.0), `comb_b_amount` (0..1, default 0.25), `comb_b_freq` (default 61.74)<br/>- bus number conventionally 16 (stereo, so 16+17)<br/>- compiled `sw_sampler_fx.scsyndef` lives in `synthesis/synthdefs/`<br/>- SC-side test verifies non-silent output for a known impulse input and frequency-domain check that 61.74 Hz comb peak is present when `comb_b_amount > 0` |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:100:| CCS-012 | Implement `sampler_dispatch.py` that converts a `(SampleRecord, PerformanceIntent, params)` tuple into the OSC bundle (`/s_new sw_sampler ...` + buffer-pool acquire) and ships it to scsynth. | MUST | T1 | - `dispatch_sample(record, intent, *, position, position_rate, grain_size_ms, density, pitch_transpose, amp, fx_send) -> SamplerHandle` issues `/b_allocRead` (if needed), `/s_new sw_sampler ...` and returns a handle for later `/n_set gate 0` release<br/>- correlates `record.gain_db` with `amp`<br/>- handles per-mode effects presets (delay_time / verb_mix / freeze / comb_b vary by mode)<br/>- tests with mock OSC client verify correct bundle ordering, gate-release path, and per-mode preset application |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:101:| CCS-013 | Per-voice gate-controlled lifecycle: composer can `play_sampler(record, duration_sec)` for fire-and-forget OR `start_sampler(record) -> handle; stop_sampler(handle)` for sustained voices. | MUST | T1 | - `sampler_dispatch.play_sampler(record, duration_sec, **params)` schedules a fire-and-forget grain cloud with an internal envelope of `duration_sec`<br/>- `start_sampler` / `stop_sampler` returns/uses a handle for sustained sampler voices that match the bowed/pad lifecycle<br/>- both code paths feed through the same `dispatch_sample` core<br/>- tests verify both lifecycles and that they can run concurrently without buffer-id collision |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:102:| CCS-014 | Integrate sampler effects bus into `master_bus.py` mix slot with appropriate gain staging (peak-normalized, not RMS) and post-mix compression bypass to preserve grain transients. | MUST | T1 | - `master_bus.apply_master_bus_scene` recognizes a `sampler_bus` mix slot with default gain -3 dB (peak-normalized so quieter library samples don't disappear)<br/>- post-mix compression for the sampler slot has `compression_ratio = 1.5` (lower than the 4.0 used elsewhere) so grain transients survive<br/>- tests verify gain staging on a known-amplitude input and grain-transient preservation via peak-vs-RMS ratio |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:114:| CCS-026 | Add per-mode effects-bus presets: solitary/evening favor more reverb + delay; working_ambience uses minimal effects; storm uses high freeze + heavy comb-B. | MUST | T1 | - `sampler_dispatch::FX_PRESETS_BY_MODE: dict[str, dict]` mapping mode name to fx args<br/>- solitary: `delay_time=0.6, delay_feedback=0.65, verb_mix=0.45, freeze_amount=0.2, comb_b_amount=0.4`<br/>- companion: `delay_time=0.5, delay_feedback=0.4, verb_mix=0.3, freeze_amount=0.0, comb_b_amount=0.15`<br/>- working_ambience: `delay_time=0.3, delay_feedback=0.2, verb_mix=0.15, freeze_amount=0.0, comb_b_amount=0.1`<br/>- evening_reflection: `delay_time=0.7, delay_feedback=0.55, verb_mix=0.5, freeze_amount=0.15, comb_b_amount=0.3`<br/>- storm: `delay_time=0.25, delay_feedback=0.7, verb_mix=0.25, freeze_amount=0.55, comb_b_amount=0.6`<br/>- tests verify each preset, that values are within SynthDef-acceptable ranges, and that `dispatch_sample` correctly applies the preset for the active mode |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:121:| CCS-033 | Update `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` to reflect the quintet, document the sampler architecture in `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md`, and add a one-page artistic-intent doc `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-artistic-intent.md`. | MUST | T2 | - musicianship roadmap mentions the quintet and sampler-as-memory<br/>- architecture doc covers the data model, daemon, dispatch, effects bus, and selector<br/>- artistic-intent doc captures the three usages (memory of place, self-quotation, found library) and the five principles<br/>- docs link from each other; mkdocs / repo nav updated if applicable |
