my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:7:The window is a string instrument. The case is a drum. The room is a resonating body. The contact mics are pickups. The Perform VE is the effects chain. The speakers are the projection. The Theramini is the guest soloist. Everything is already sounding. The system's job is to listen first, then add what's missing.
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:41:The same math — oscillation, envelope, modulation — governs all of these. A grain cloud with density modulated at 0.5Hz IS a rhythmic pattern. A phrase with pitch modulated over 25 days IS a narrative arc. The architecture should reflect this unity.
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:57:At control rate (0.1-20Hz), an Oscillator modulates other Oscillators (tremolo, vibrato, filter sweep).
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:74:│   │   │   ├── waveform: grain_cloud | physical_model | spectral_response | captured
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:75:│   │   │   ├── ControlOscillator (0.1-20Hz) — vibrato, tremolo, filter modulation
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:214:- Choose intervals: descending minor third (tenderness), sustained (stillness), with rain-like grain texture
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:251:- The grain engine respects CPU limits — reduce density before dropping frames
