my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:37:**Phase 2 — Core rule stack (CCH-011..CCH-021).** R1 Metric Accent, R2 Phrase Arch (Todd/KTH parabolic), R3 Agogic Accent, R4 Duration Contrast, R5 Final Ritardando (Friberg–Sundberg square-root), R6 Punctuation+Breath, R7 Articulation Shaping, R8 Microtiming Polish (below JND). Role-filter gating so grid-locked voices skip the stack. Phrase-feature extraction via partitura. End-of-phase: single-voice melodic passages sound shaped, not flat; metric gate shows structured deviations vs. flat-line baseline.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:69:- **New** `my-claw/tests/test_render_*.py` — per-rule, role-filter, replay, ablation, metric, anti-pattern tests
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:79:| CCH-005 | Define Role enum (ostinato/melody/pad/perc/accent/silence) with grid_locked flag and role-filter policy used by all rules. | MUST | T1 | - Role enum exists with grid_locked boolean attribute (ostinato=True, perc=True, melody=False, pad=False, accent=False, silence=N/A)<br/>- every rule in the stack respects a shared `rule.applies_to(role)` filter so grid-locked voices skip R1–R8<br/>- tests verify grid-locked voices emerge from the render pass with timing_deviation_ms == 0 and no microtiming jitter |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:85:| CCH-011 | Build the RenderPass framework: ordered rule stack with stable order, per-rule enable flags, per-rule quantity k, and role-filter gating. | MUST | T1 | - `render/pass_.py` defines RenderPass(rules, enabled_flags, quantities) with apply(score_tree, seeds) → PerformedPart<br/>- rule order is fixed and documented: R1→R2→R3→R4→R5→R6→R7→R8→R9→R10→R11→R12<br/>- per-rule k defaults to 1.0; authoring surface exposes overrides per-piece and per-intent-tag<br/>- tests verify stable order, k=0 equals rule-disabled, k=1 equals calibrated default |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:86:| CCH-012 | Implement R1 Metric Accent: per-beat-position velocity multiplier applied only to non-grid-locked melodic/accent voices. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/metric_accent.py` applies 16-step 4/4 table [1.00, 0.82, 0.92, 0.80, 0.95, 0.80, 0.90, 0.78, 0.97, 0.80, 0.91, 0.78, 0.94, 0.80, 0.90, 0.78] with meter-aware extension to 3/4, 6/8, 5/4, 7/8<br/>- rule skips ostinato + perc by role filter<br/>- tests verify velocity distribution matches table on 4/4 melodic passage and is unchanged on ostinato |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:94:| CCH-020 | Enforce role-filter gating across R1–R8 with a single shared contract; verify machine identity preservation end-to-end. | MUST | T1 | - all R1–R8 rules check `rule.applies_to(event.role)` before mutating the event<br/>- integration test: ostinato + melody passage renders with melody shaped and ostinato exactly quantized<br/>- gate test: passage where ostinato has non-zero timing_deviation_ms fails (indicates a rule leaked) |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:153:- **Forgetting machine identity.** If a rule leaks onto grid-locked voices, the render fails the role-filter gate.
